<m0>  JUPITER (--) (AP) (--) The St. Louis Cardinals will join the Montreal Expos in a new spring training complex in South Florida.<ep>
   Palm Beach County commissioners agreed Tuesday to negotiate a 20-year spring training lease with the Expos and Cardinals for a planned $25 million stadium to be built in Jupiter with hotel tax money. It would open in time for the 1998 season.<ep>
   The Cardinals have trained in St. Petersburg since 1938.<ql>
